document_data.Abilities:
Iahn was an imaskari vengeance taker. He carried one of the 21 [[Damos]] of Deep Imaskar, which was the source of some of his supernatural abilities.{{cite book/Darkvision|89}} He most often used it to gain unique insights.{{cite book/Darkvision|7-9}}

He was also able to use some spells, likely ''[[blur]]'', ''[[dimension door]]'',{{cite book/Darkvision|45}} and ''[[invisibility]]''.{{cite book/Darkvision|226}} Disguises fashioned by Iahn included some components of illusion magic.{{cite book/Darkvision|110-111}} He was sensitive to flows of magic.{{cite book/Darkvision|112}} One of his daily protective spells warned him when under unseen observation.{{cite book/Darkvision|116}}

Despite the diminished martial instruction available in Deep Imaskar,{{cite book/Underdark|139}} Iahn was an excellent fighter even by the standards of other races.
He wielded a repeating crossbow and a dagger that split between a stiletto and a butterfly knife.

document_data.Apprehending Ususi Manaallin:
As of the spring of {{yearlink|1374}}, he had been on Ususi Manaallin's trail for two months.{{cite book/Darkvision|5}}
When he caught up to her coach wagon, he found several creatures that attacked him; upon slaying them, he learned they served [[Pandorym]].
When he followed into the ruin she was visiting at the time, a trap she left unsprung captured him;{{cite book/Darkvision|58}} on her way back, she took the opportunity to interrogate him.{{cite book/Darkvision|60}} She learned Deep Imaskar was under attack, and her expertise with the Celestial Nadir was required to prevent it.{{cite book/Darkvision|87}}
She convinced Iahn to travel with her to Vaelan, in order to find an entrance to the Nadir, instead of returning directly to Deep Imaskar.{{cite book/Darkvision|91}}

In Vaelan, Iahn and Ususi investigated the Body Shop.{{cite book/Darkvision|110}} There, Iahn discovered a lurking, hostile presence within the plangent shopkeeper. Shortly after, the two of them encountered [[Datharathi#Eined Datharathi|Eined Datharathi]]. She wanted their help stopping the production of Datharathi crystal; they accepted, though they only intended to seek an entrance to the Celestial Nadir.
The three of them chartered a ship towards Adama's Tooth, where they were confronted by [[Datharathi#Shaddon Datharathi|Shaddon Datharathi]].{{cite book/Darkvision|219}}
The wizard slew Eined,{{cite book/Darkvision|223}} and the two deep imaskari fought him; unable to slay him, they fled for an entrance to the Celestial Nadir.{{cite book/Darkvision|228-229}}

In the demiplane, they encountered [[Datharathi#Warian Datharathi|Warian Datharathi]] and [[Datharathi#Zeltaebar Datharathi|Zeltaebar Datharathi]].{{cite book/Darkvision|251}}
Finding a path into the Palace of the Purple Emperor, they were briefly detained by a trap.{{cite book/Darkvision|275}}
[[Prince Monolith]] and [[Kiril Duskmourn]] rescued them from it; after they joined, the six of them headed for the Imperial Weapons Cache.{{cite book/Darkvision|282-284}}
There, Iahn would fight the forces of Pandorym, using a crossbow he liberated from the very cache.{{cite book/Darkvision|299-300}}
